Here's how to handle each scenario with modern MSTest (3.9+/3.10+):

## 1. Windows-only tests — `[OSCondition]`

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[OSCondition(OperatingSystems.Windows)]
public void WindowsRegistry_ReadsExpectedValue()
{
    var value = Registry.GetValue(@"HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\MyApp", "Setting", null);
    Assert.IsNotNull(value);
}
```

## 2. Skip in CI — `[CICondition]`

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[CICondition(ConditionMode.Exclude)]
public void GpuRendering_ProducesExpectedOutput()
{
    var result = GpuRenderer.Render(scene);
    Assert.IsNotNull(result);
}
```

## 3. Flaky external API — `[Retry]`

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[Retry(3)]
[Timeout(10000)]
public async Task WeatherApi_ReturnsForecast()
{
    var forecast = await _weatherClient.GetForecastAsync(_testContext.CancellationToken);
    Assert.IsNotNull(forecast);
}
```

Use `[Retry]` only for genuinely flaky external dependencies—not to mask race conditions.

## 4. Cleanup even on failure — `[TestCleanup]`

```csharp
[TestClass]
public sealed class TempFileTests
{
    private string _tempFilePath = string.Empty;

    [TestInitialize]
    public void Setup()
    {
        _tempFilePath = Path.GetTempFileName();
    }

    [TestMethod]
    public void ProcessFile_WritesExpectedContent()
    {
        FileProcessor.Process(_tempFilePath);
        var content = File.ReadAllText(_tempFilePath);
        Assert.Contains("expected", content);
    }

    [TestCleanup]
    public void Cleanup()
    {
        // Runs even if the test fails
        if (File.Exists(_tempFilePath))
            File.Delete(_tempFilePath);
    }
}
```

Alternatively, implement `IDisposable` on the test class — MSTest calls `Dispose` after each test (after `[TestCleanup]`).

---

**Minimum versions:** `[Retry]` requires MSTest 3.9+, `[OSCondition]`/`[CICondition]` require MSTest 3.10+. `[TestCleanup]` works in all versions.
